Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join, downturning. Clay medium, micaceous, red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp; double stamped.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0446)
